{"TopicId":203015,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"ESA is hiring new astronauts - has anyone here applied?","CreatedByName":"michal.don","CreatedById":150623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T19:34:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"michal.don","CreatedById":150623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T19:34:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs the title says, I\u0027m just curious, if anyone of us space nerds took it to another level and answered the call \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T20:01:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny known astronaut playing KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"michal.don","CreatedById":150623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T20:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNone that I\u0027m aware of, that\u0027s why I was asking, I was kind of hoping it might change soon, I think quite a few of\u00A0the KSP players would be eligible for the position \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T21:26:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they are taking old, out of shape non-scientists that are 6\u00277\u0022 or so and who live in America... Count me in!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T21:58:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe if I was 20 years younger...\u00A0 \u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988278\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623528062\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny known astronaut playing KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure... possibly...\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut I know of one absolutely confirmed ESA Scientist who\u00A0plays KSP\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allow=\u0022accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/index.html\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/gC567NTNbrI?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhelperdude","CreatedById":204462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T22:00:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could mayyybe apply in the\u00A0future, since I also live in a major ESA-member state,\u00A0but I think I will go into the astronomy direction later in my life\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T22:05:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have at least 5 years before I can start applying, and that\u0027d be on the NASA side of the pond.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ben J. Kerman","CreatedById":204948,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T22:25:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623535253\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204462\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhelperdude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Starhelperdude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could mayyybe apply in the\u00A0future, since I also live in a major ESA-member state,\u00A0but I think I will go into the astronomy direction later in my life\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI live in the US, am still too young, and am thinking more along the lines of \u003Cstrong\u003Eaerospace engineering as a career\u003C/strong\u003E rather than actually being an astronaut.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhelperdude","CreatedById":204462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-12T22:35:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623536757\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204948\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ben J. Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Ben J. Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI live in the US, am still too young, and am thinking more along the lines of \u003Cstrong\u003Eaerospace engineering as a career\u003C/strong\u003E rather than actually being an astronaut.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m also too young sadly, though that means that I can still think about what I will do later in my life, either rocket engineer stuff or astronomy stuff, specified in extrasolar stuff like neutron stars and black holes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-13T00:00:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Project Scientist for \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/140271-nasas-osiris-rex/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EOSIRIS-REx \u003C/a\u003Ealso plays KSP and is active on the forum as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/9417-ionstorm/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00229417\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/9417-ionstorm/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IonStorm\u003C/a\u003E. Incidentally, Dr. Brian May of \u003Cem\u003EQueen\u003C/em\u003E is also involved in the project, IIRC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://arstechnica.com/science/2018/12/video-astronaut-scott-kelly-teaches-orbital-mechanics-with-kerbal-space-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAstronaut Scott Kelly has also played KSP while being interviewed by Lee Hutchinson of Arstechnica.com\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-13T00:21:24Z\u0022 title=\u002206/13/2021 12:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 13, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IonStorm","CreatedById":9417,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-13T01:38:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623542401\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Project Scientist for \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/140271-nasas-osiris-rex/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EOSIRIS-REx \u003C/a\u003Ealso plays KSP and is active on the forum as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/9417-ionstorm/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00229417\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/9417-ionstorm/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IonStorm\u003C/a\u003E. Incidentally, Dr. Brian May of \u003Cem\u003EQueen\u003C/em\u003E is also involved in the project, IIRC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://arstechnica.com/science/2018/12/video-astronaut-scott-kelly-teaches-orbital-mechanics-with-kerbal-space-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAstronaut Scott Kelly has also played KSP while being interviewed by Lee Hutchinson of Arstechnica.com\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, I got hooked from one of Scott Manley\u0027s KSP videos in 2011 since I was following him due to his wonderful asteroid orbit\u00A0visualizations, though I\u0027m a sloppy KSP player myself.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/96415-jasonden/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002296415\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/96415-jasonden/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022font-size:13.5px;padding:.1em .8em;\u0022\u003E@Jasonden\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis a deputy PI for Dragonfly and he plays KSP and is active on the forums.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBrian May likes making stereo pairs.\u00A0 This one from two images at different times from the same camera was a challenge for him to make, but is informative\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.asteroidmission.org/stereopair/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.asteroidmission.org/stereopair/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy PhD is in biochemistry, but I apply it to planetary science.\u00A0 I\u0027ve never been to space but did have the amazing opportunity to\u00A0briefly work with Kate Rubins on the DNA sequencer on the ISS and talk with Leland Melvin about research,\u00A0but I didn\u0027t ask him about his dogs.\u00A0 Starting your journey to space research or technology at a young age is awesome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}